Valentino teaches those personal memories as trophies of his social ascent: from humble dressmaker of the city of Voghera, in northern Italy, to idol of the international "jet-set".
There's nothing wrong with being in love with royalty.
"At least they don't turn off their cigarette butts on your magnificent carpet like some beautiful pop music celebrities do," says Baroness Fiona Thyssen-Bornemisza.
In the '60s and '70s, we both lived in the Alps and were good friends.
